SEARCH
Module dbConnect
Package dbConnect.execution

Class RetrieveParser

java.lang.Object
dbConnect.execution.RetrieveParser
public class RetrieveParser extends Object
Handle retrieval query (select query) parsing using reflection. This class also contains overload for getting all data.

  • Method Details

    • retrieve

      public <T> List<T> retrieve(Class<T> modelClass, String whereTerm, Object... params) throws IllegalAccessException, SQLException
      A method invokes DBQuery.loadData(String, DBMapper, Object...) to fetch data from a Class model .
      Type Parameters:
      T - Class
      Parameters:
      modelClass - a Data Model Class. It must contain a method call getTable(). It must contain a method call getMap().
      whereTerm - conditions used for the search. Values are stored in params and is parsed where placeholder marking ? is placed.
      params - values of whereTerm store in corresponding order.
      Returns:
      a List of instances specified by the data model class that met the whereTerm conditions.
      Throws:
      IllegalAccessException - when missing getTable() or getMap() method from the data model.
      SQLException - when there is an error occurred during data selection.

    • retrieveAll

      public <T> List<T> retrieveAll(Class<T> modelClass) throws IllegalAccessException, SQLException
      A method invokes DBQuery.loadData(String, DBMapper, Object...) to fetch all data from a Class model. This simply involk retrieve(Class, String, Object...) with no whereTerm condition.
      Type Parameters:
      T - Class
      Parameters:
      modelClass - a Data Model Class. It must contain a method call getTable(). It must contain a method call getMap().
      Returns:
      a List of all instances specified by the data model class.
      Throws:
      IllegalAccessException - when missing getTable() or getMap() method from the data model.
      SQLException - when there is an error occurred during data selection.
